</span><p>When planning content, don't forget to create guidelines for any communication between your employees and customers, including the attitude and way your staff should approach and communicate with customers.</p></div></div></div><div
id="how-to-create-a-brand-identity-section1-step6" class="step"><div
class="step-desc"><div
class="step-title">
<span>1.6&nbsp;</span><h4 id=monitor-your-brand>Monitor your brand.</h4></div><div
class="image-wrapper"><div
class="image-holder">
<img
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-brand-identity-monitor-your-brand-288x288-2023014.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=144&dpr=2" class="lazyload" width="144" height="144" alt="Monitor your brand."></div></div><p>Once you've launched your new brand identity, start tracking your brand to find out where it is mentioned, what is being said about it, and to understand how it is being perceived. This, in turn, will help you identify misconceptions and areas for improvement, giving you the opportunity to make any necessary changes.</p><p>There is a range of services available for tracking brand mentions, including Google Analytics, Brandwatch, and Sprout Social.</p></div></div></div></div> <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http://schema.org","@type":"HowTo","name":"How to Create a Brand Identity","description":"<p>Creating a winning and memorable brand identity shouldn't be difficult if you know the key elements of your company. It is also a fun and exciting process, as you will be defining and bringing to life your company's personality. <br>\nHere are six steps for creating a brand identity.<\/p>\n","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-how-to-create-a-brand-identity-completed-800x800-2023014.jpeg?crop=1:1,smart&width=250&dpr=2","height":"800","width":"800"},"estimatedCost":{"@type":"MonetaryAmount","currency":"USD","value":"0.00"},"totalTime":"P1M","step":[{"@type":"HowToSection","position":"1","name":"<p>Creating a brand identity.<\/p>\n","itemListElement":[{"@type":"HowToStep","position":"1","name":"<p>Do some research.<\/p>\n","text":"<p>The first step in creating a brand identity is conducting research to learn about your target audience, determine what differentiates your products and\/or services from competitors, and understand the marketplace in which you are competing. Then, perform a <a href=\"#what-is-a-swot-analysis\">SWOT analysis<\/a>.<\/p>\n","url":"https://www.zarla.com/guides/how-to-create-a-brand-iden